    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Miklós Oláh (Linz, 23 April 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He has understood from his letter of the 19<hi rend="super">th</hi> of
                            this month that Oláh sees it best if he decides due to András Báthori’s
                            illness and answers what he has been entrusted with. He has signed the
                            letters that he wrote to Giovanni Battista Castaldo, Pál Bornemissza,
                            and Georg Werner about holding the joint assembly with Transylvania in
                            Báthori’s absence, and he sends it together with the letters of
                            accreditation so he can furnish it with the Hungarian seal. He responded
                            to Báthori’s idea that it will be possible to implement it as soon as he
                            returns. Oláh should prepare the letters and send them to Transylvania
                            via mail.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Ferdinandus etc. Reverendissime in Christo Pater Fidelis Sincere
                    Dilecte!</p>
                <p>Ex litteris tuis die 19. praesentis mensis ad nos datis<note
                        type="critic">We do not know this letter.</note> clementer intelleximus ea,
                    quae tibi visa sunt, ut nos propter spectabilis et magnifici <del
                        corresp="scriba">Andreae iudici</del>
                    <persName>Andreae de Bathor</persName><note type="critic">András (Bonaventura)
                        Báthori.</note> aegritudinem, in quam denuo incidit, ordinaremus, quaeque ad <choice>
                        <orig>tuis</orig>
                        <supplied>tuas</supplied>
                    </choice> litteras, quas una nobis transmisisti, <del corresp="scriba"
                        >ordinaremus</del> responderemus. <del corresp="scriba">Probato</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">Probat</add> itaque <del corresp="scriba">isti
                        suo</del> gratiose istiusmodi consilio et opinione tua, litteras per te ad
                    spectabilem et magnificum <persName>Ioannem Baptistam Castaldum</persName>,<note
                        type="critic">Giovanni Battista Castaldo.</note> bellicum locumtenentem,
                    necnon consiliarios nostros reverendissimum <persName>Paulum episcopum
                        Vesprimiensiem</persName><note type="critic">Pál Bornemissza.</note> et
                    egregium <persName>Georgium Vernerum</persName><note type="critic">Georg
                        Werner.</note> de conventu <del corresp="scriba">in</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">cum</add> Transsylvania ab eis absente
                        <persName>Bathory</persName> celebrando confectas, simulque litteras
                    credentiales manu nostra subsignavimus, tibique illas sigillo nostro Hungarico
                    ulterius expediendas remittimus. <del corresp="scriba">Ipsique</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">Ipsi</add> vera <persName>Bathory</persName>
                    iuxta <del corresp="scriba">formulam pro te quaque tuam</del> conceptum, quod
                    nobis transmisit, respondemus hoc solum modo <milestone unit="pb"/>addito, quod,
                    quo ad reditum suum audiveram, daturi sumus, ut quamprimum possibile fuerit ei
                    satisfactio facit. Restat igitur, ut litteras praedictas quamprimum expedias et
                    per postam celeriter in Transsylvaniam transmittas. Vestram in eo ex<gap
                        extent="1" reason="illegible" unit="word"/> exsecuturus voluntatem. </p>
                <p>Datum in oppido nostro <placeName>Lynczio</placeName> die 23. Aprilis
                    1552.</p>
                <p><hi rend="italic"
                        ><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>Probably<?oxy_custom_end?>
                        on the outer side:</hi> Agriensi.</p>
                
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
